            . I am a beadle. I stopped the prisoner in Russell-square - I had seen him loitering about; he went into Torrington-street three times - I went up and found these pots on him.</p>
               <p>EDWARD SMITH. I <rs id="t18270531-266-viclabel1438" type="occupation">keep a public-house</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270531-266-victim1469 t18270531-266-viclabel1438"></join> in Torrington-street. This is my pot.</p>
               <p>The prisoner put in a written Defence, stating that he had found the pots in Bloomsbury-square, and representing himself to be in great distress.</p>
